Defendant in custody.
The defendant is sentenced to the Wisconsin State Prison System for a total of twelve (12) years. That is five (5) years initial confinement followed by seven (7) years extended supervision.
Conditions of extended supervision:
1) Pay court costs;
2) pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC;
3) assessment, counseling, treatment as deemed appropriate by the Departments assessment process;
4) comply with sex offender registry and treatment;
5) maintain fulltime employment/schooling/combination;
6) have no contact with anyone under the age of 18 unless approved by the agent;
7) have no contact with the victim, W.E.D.
The Court finds the defendant not eligible for both the Challenge Incarceration Program and the Substance Abuse Program.
Credit is given for 276 days.  (The parties stipulate to this amount)
Minutes.

